<br>
Quoting the article that Nacros' referred to:<br>
<br>
&quot;A common misconception is that &quot;IP spoofing&quot; can be used to hide your IP address while surfing the Internet, chatting on-line, sending e-mail, and so forth. This is generally not true. Forging the source IP address causes the responses to be misdirected, meaning you cannot create a normal network connection. However, IP spoofing is an integral part of many network attacks that do not need to see responses (blind spoofing). &quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
M'kay. So, yeah, Nakros was justified in calling Trinity out about the general concept of spoofing. But he was off if you consider that Trinity was referring to (in a self-admitted non-expert manner) the ISSUE AT HAND.<br>
<br>
Spoofing would, essentially be next to impossible when logging onto our message boards, it's simply not an option. We're not talking about IP authentication here. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=151946" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.brackish.org/frot.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub27.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=frotttty>frotttty</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:pink;'>Tavern Floor Sweeper</span></span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(2/2/03 5:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3092.topic&index=82>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spoofing IP's</span><hr size=1> Sad, arkadian -<br>
<br>
You are just as guilty of what you are condemning the officers for. You are claiming that they spoke without &quot;proof.&quot; <br>
<br>
Perhaps you //meant// they didn't prove what they are saying, but you were assuming that they didn't have that proof and that it wasn't a case of simply not bringing it to the foreground of the accusations.<br>
<br>
And from reading the thread, it's good to see someone bring up Occam's Razor.<br>
<br>
You have to look at agendas, and who has what to gain. <br>
<br>
One of the few things that Isengard officers could *possibly* have to gain by implicating someone is a sense of well being in the guild. That the perpetrator has been caught and we are safe again. That they are the heros. But honestly, who cares about this?<br>
<br>
HERE's where I'd apply the &quot;it's only a game&quot; bit. This isn't national security. This isn't a war that we've declared won, the bad guys jailed or held at bay.<br>
<br>
That's fair... but it doesn't have anything to do with the &quot;maybe the officers perpetrated it.&quot;<br>
<br>
And you'd honestly have to be a little bit brain-light if you didn't associate Megara's &quot;maybe Malkier did it to blame me&quot; bit with: &quot;BLAME MALKIER and CO. FOR THIS,&quot; it's essentially the seed of doubt she was lamely attempting to plant.<br>
<br>
The protection about not having the knowhow to destroy the site from Brena is what makes me believe that it was Megara and not Brena that did it, but it's all the same camp. Besides, it doesn't take an electronics specialist to break a VCR (the only interface you need to know is, perhaps, a hammer).<br>
<br>
Anyway, Megara is just sitting back and watching the show. She's been called out on so many levels of honor, so many fits of paradox and contradiction and hypocrisy that it's evident that the &quot;game&quot; that is EQ extends to these boards, and etc.<br>
<br>
Yeah, we'll make a better site. Yeah, the world hasn't stopped. Etc. This is all secondary to the game that has extended into these boards. How you play that game is irrelevant.<br>
<br>
Hmm anything else? Nope that about wraps it up. I don't think anyone except Meg &amp; Co. need to apologise and own up to their behaviors. Arkadian, I hope any conflicts that you might have seen have been unraveled and been explained: noone in Isengard is &quot;out to get&quot; anyone, that the accusers become the accused is quite ridiculous, especially that anyone would implicate Aeroes is foolish. <br>
<br>
